    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-23T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="663"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d663">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">638.5131/49: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-23T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 23, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. Your 37, May 21, noon. We spoke with the French Chargé d’Affaires about this
                    matter today, pointing out that there appeared to be a satisfactory basis for a
                    commercial agreement between France and Haiti on the lines of the <hi
                        rend="italic">avenant</hi> of last year, and stating that for Haiti to
                    attempt to meet the present demands of the French Government would inevitably
                    result in serious financial and economic disorder in Haiti, thereby destroying
                    the progress obtained through the assistance of the United States in accordance
                    with the 1915 Treaty<note n="36" xml:id="d663fn36">Signed September 16, 1915,
                            <ref target="frus1915#pg_449">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relation</hi>, 1915, p. 449</ref>.</note> in
                    placing the finances of Haiti on a sound basis.</p>
                <p>The Chargé d’Affaires said he would cable his Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
